## 3. The 4-state UX hook (mandatory for every encrypted interaction)

Every confidential write/read in the UI MUST surface these four states. Skipping any one of them produces "ghost transactions" where the user has no idea whether their encrypted input is in flight.

| State | Component cue | What's happening under the hood |
|-------|---------------|-------------------------------|
| `idle` | Form is enabled, button reads "Submit". | No relayer activity. |
| `encrypting` | Button reads "Encrypting…", spinner; form locked. | Relayer SDK is FHE-encrypting the input client-side. Cancellable. |
| `pending` | Button reads "Confirming on-chain…"; tx hash link visible. | Tx broadcast; waiting for inclusion + relayer indexing. |
| `decrypted` | Result rendered (or "Encrypted — only you can decrypt"). | Either user-side decryption succeeded, or oracle callback fired, or the slot is permanently encrypted to this viewer. |

**Reference hook signature** (use this exact shape for consistency across components):

```ts
type UxState = "idle" | "encrypting" | "pending" | "decrypted";

interface ConfidentialAction<T> {
  state: UxState;
  result: T | null;
  error: Error | null;
  txHash: `0x${string}` | null;
  run: (input: unknown) => Promise<void>;
  reset: () => void;
}
```

